item.dc:creator: @Jddogg9 Jddogg9
item.description:
@Jddogg9 wrote:

haha just found the error… i’m slow :S… guess i made a typo inside of it[quote="_™, post:6, topic:290758"][quote author=Jddogg9 link=topic=384402.msg2883713#msg2883713 date=1248471285]

I think it’s because your “I” in “IOExceptionF” needs to be like this “i” but I’m not sure. I had this error with a portal to. It was wrote: Cannot find symbol to. It was in “ToX”. I changed it to “toX” and it worked.

i’ll try that, but i’ve just encountered this error…

never had it before… and there arel like tons of “IOExceptionF” 's in client.java…[br][br][size=1]Posted on: July 24, 2009, 03:35:31 pm[/size][hr]and can someone explain what “IOExceptionF”

and what caused the error? It’s been totally fine till now…
[/quote]

He made a typo… It’s IOException, but it must be imported.[/quote]

thanks _tm
